Module com.example.bank_teller

Package com.example.bank_teller

package com.example.bank_teller
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    Account
    Abstract class that represents a generic account with three fields: a profile object containing the full name and dob of the account holder, a boolean specifying if the account is closed or not, and the balance in the account.
    AccountDatabase
    Represents database all bank accounts using an array of Accounts.
    BankTellerController
    A GUI class to process the transactions (opening or closing an account, depositing into or withdrawing from an existing account, or printing account details) entered by the user through the graphical user interface and outputs the results to the text area present in the GUI.
    BankTellerMain
    The main class which extends the javafx.application.Application class.
    Checking
    Represents a specific type of account: a regular checking account.
    CollegeChecking
    Represents a specific type of checking account: college checking account.
    Date
    Represents a calender date with three fields: day, month, and year.
    MoneyMarket
    Represents a specific type of checking account: money market savings account.
    Profile
    Represents a Profile with three fields: the account holder's first name, last name, and date of birth
    RunProject2
    This class calls the BankTeller class and starts running the bank service.
    Savings
    Represents a specific type of checking account: regular savings account.
